# <type>(<optional scope>): <subject — imperative, lowercase, no period>
#
# Why this change matters (the diff already shows the what). Wrap at 72 cols.
#
# Refs: <work order, issue, or doc — optional>
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Allowed types:
#   feat       new user-facing capability
#   fix        bug fix
#   refactor   code shape change; behaviour unchanged
#   perf       measurable performance win
#   test       tests added or fixed
#   docs       README, CHANGELOG, comments, work orders
#   style      whitespace / formatting only
#   chore      build, deps, tooling, version bump
#   revert     undoing a prior commit
#   security   vulnerability fix, data handling, crypto changes
#
# Atomic commit rules (CONTRIBUTING.md):
#   1. One logical concern per commit.
#   2. Builds and tests on its own (`npm run build && npm test`).
#   3. Revertable independently.
#   4. If "and" appears in your subject, it's probably two commits.
#
# Co-authored commits end with:
#   Co-Authored-By: ClaudeCode <noreply@anthropic.com>
